<p><strong>The Cinema Book: 3rd Edition PDF - Questions and Answers</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. What is The Cinema Book?</strong></p>
<p>The Cinema Book is a comprehensive guide to the history, theory, and practice of cinema. Now in its third edition, it has been updated and expanded to include the latest developments in the field. The book is divided into seven parts covering: the origins of cinema; the history of cinema; cinematic techniques; film theory; film criticism; and contemporary cinema.</p>
<p><strong>2. Who is the author of The Cinema Book?</strong></p>
<p>The Cinema Book is written by David Bordwell and Kristin Thompson. Bordwell is a professor of film at the University of Wisconsin-Madison and Thompson is a professor of film at the University of California, Santa Barbara. Together, they are the authors of numerous books and articles on cinema.</p>
